The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, June 28: Steel Authority of India Ltd today sanctioned eight projects, which would cost about Rs 300 crore. Out of these, three have been cleared for Bokaro Steel, two for Rourkela Steel and one each for Bhilai Steel, Durgapur Steel and Visvesvaraya Iron amp; Steel in Bhadravati. These are in addition to the capital schemes valued at over Rs 3,000 crore, which are under various stages of implementation.

 New Delhi, June 28: Hindustan Motors today said it has completed the transfer of its component business into a separate subsidiary, Avtec. Private equity investor Actis will hold a 30 per cent stake in Avtec.

 Calcutta, June 28: The Securities and Exchange Board of India has extended the supersession of the Calcutta Stock Exchange committee till March 2006.

 New Delhi, June 28: The government today reconstituted the central direct taxes advisory committee under the chairmanship of finance minister P. Chidambaram. Along with 16 non-official members, the committee will include secretary, department of revenue, central board of direct taxes? chairman and member (revenue).

 New Delhi, June 28: In a bid to avoid flash strikes in the oil industry, the government today declared services in such industries as public utilities for another six months.




